\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Evaluating dynamic access**\\n\\nI'm considering the user's request for dynamic access and whether it’s okay to directly access library internals with the active class. I think I should clear the cache before calling toJSON to ensure everything follows the natural path. There might be a need to remove the MethodHandle test if it's not working. The repository examples use reflection for compiler-generated classes, but I need to remember that the user likely expects a straightforward cache clear before the public API flow. This raises potential problems in a native image where static final fields aren't truly final.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Assessing test metadata**\\n\\nI'm trying to figure out if the test generates any metadata, and it seems like the Forge agent might handle that. But for a native run, metadata should be intact. I realize the metadata under src/test/resources shouldn't be changed. For existing tests, they use `getDeclaredField` on library classes, which the native image can support if the agent generates it. After clearing the cache, if `getMethods()` starts with methods from SampleObject and the cache is empty, it’ll trigger class operations. I’m contemplating whether we need to refine this to one test and if the MethodHandle test is truly necessary.\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_7QekuptsDG1qqehlfN5Q8kDQ|fc_0a040482419b381b0169f941c39c3881969de1252a52fa1089", "name": "edit", "arguments": {"path": "tests/src/org.mortbay.jetty/jetty-util/6.1.26/src/test/java/org_mortbay_jetty/jetty_util/JSONObjectConvertorTest.java", "edits": [{"oldText": "import java.lang.invoke.MethodHandle;\nimport java.lang.invoke.MethodHandles;\nimport java.lang.invoke.MethodType;\nimport java.util.Map;", "newText": "import java.lang.reflect.Field;\nimport java.util.Map;"}, {"oldText": "public class JSONObjectConvertorTest {\n    @Test\n    void compilerGeneratedClassLookupResolvesObjectType() throws Throwable {\n        final MethodHandle classLookup = MethodHandles.privateLookupIn(JSONObjectConvertor.class, MethodHandles.lookup())\n                .findStatic(JSONObjectConvertor.class, \"class$\", MethodType.methodType(Class.class, String.class));\n\n        final Class<?> resolvedClass = (Class<?>) classLookup.invoke(Object.class.getName());\n\n        assertThat(resolvedClass).isEqualTo(Object.class);\n    }\n\n    @Test\n    void toJSONDiscoversAndInvokesPublicGetterMethods() {", "newText": "public class JSONObjectConvertorTest {\n    @Test\n    void toJSONDiscoversAndInvokesPublicGetterMethods() throws Exception {\n        clearCompilerGeneratedObjectClassCache();"}, {"oldText": "        assertThat(parsed).containsEntry(\"active\", Boolean.TRUE);\n        assertThat(parsed).doesNotContainKey(\"secret\");\n    }\n\n    public static class SampleObject {", "newText": "        assertThat(parsed).containsEntry(\"active\", Boolean.TRUE);\n        assertThat(parsed).doesNotContainKey(\"secret\");\n    }\n\n    private static void clearCompilerGeneratedObjectClassCache() throws Exception {\n        final Field field = JSONObjectConvertor.class.getDeclaredField(\"class$java$lang$Object\");\n        field.setAccessible(true);\n        field.set(null, null);\n    }\n\n    public static class SampleObject {"}]}}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 8615, "output": 1467, "cacheRead": 22016, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 32098, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "toolUse", "timestamp": 1777942961243, "responseId": "resp_0a040482419b381b0169f941b2474c8196a8f5febe166dec1a"}}
